<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="21" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,151,428]" pageId="3" pageNumber="21">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,313,152,176]" pageId="3" pageNumber="21">Remarks.</emphasis>
The new species is somewhat similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Duda, 1932" authorityName="Duda" authorityYear="1932" box="[776,1093,151,176]" class="Insecta" family="Chloropidae" genus="Chlorops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="zernyi">
<emphasis box="[776,954,152,176]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="21">Chlorops zernyi</emphasis>
Duda, 
<number box="[1037,1093,151,175]" pageId="3" pageNumber="21" value="1932.0">1932</number>
</taxonomicName>
from Europe, 
<collectingCountry box="[1258,1325,152,175]" name="Japan" pageId="3" pageNumber="21">Japan</collectingCountry>
, and west &amp; central Siberia in the ocellar triangle smooth, yellow, with a black spot in leaf shape covering the most part of the triangle and contended with the ocellar tubercle; and the shape of the gonostylus. But it can be separated from the latter by the 
<number box="[300,313,260,284]" pageId="3" pageNumber="21" value="2.0">2</number>
nd antennal segment brown; the arista black; the gena broad, about 
<number box="[1100,1149,260,284]" pageId="3" pageNumber="21" value="1.25">1.25</number>
times as high as the 
<number box="[1399,1411,260,284]" pageId="3" pageNumber="21" value="3.0">3</number>
rd antennal segment; and the palpus yellow entirely. In 
<taxonomicName authority="Duda" authorityName="Duda" box="[741,913,295,320]" class="Insecta" family="Chloropidae" genus="Chlorops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="zernyi">
<emphasis box="[741,843,296,320]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="21">C. zernyi</emphasis>
Duda
</taxonomicName>
, the 
<number box="[966,979,295,319]" pageId="3" pageNumber="21" value="2.0">2</number>
nd antennal segment is yellow; the arista is white; the gena is a little narrower than high of the 
<number box="[747,759,332,356]" pageId="3" pageNumber="21" value="3.0">3</number>
rd antennal segment; and the palpus is yellow, with black tip (
<bibRefCitation author="Kanmiya" box="[158,337,367,391]" pageId="3" pageNumber="21" refString="Kanmiya, K. (1978) Notes on the genus Chlorops Meigen (Diptera, Chloropidae) from Japan and Formosa. Kontyu, 46 (1), 52 - 76." type="journal article" year="1978">
Kanmiya, 
<number box="[277,337,367,391]" pageId="3" pageNumber="21" value="1978.0">1978</number>
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
